My mom and I came here after a grocery trip to 168 Market.
I had been wanting elote for a long time, and this place satisfied my craving.
Their elote was just okay, not too generous with the spread, but it tasted fine, so nothing to complain about.
My mom ordered strawberry crepas, it seemed thin/plain, but she shared with me and it tasted good.
Not too sweet, not too much whip cream.
While we were ordering, I felt as if the lady was rushing us so she could sit in the back room again.
There were no other customers, so I don't get it.
I would come back if I were in the area, but only to try the rest of their menu.

